Object.Field: SNP_TRT : LKM Object Storage to ADWC Copy

COMPONENT NAME: LKM File to ADWC Copy COMPONENT VERSION: 1 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 12.2.1.4.0 or above
DESCRIPTION
This LKM will load data from local or HDFS file source to Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Cloud using Oracle Object Storage as intermediate staging. The source file is first loaded into Oracle Object Storage staging area. Then we are using dbms_cloud.copy_data() to load data from Object Storage into staging table on ADWC. The user must set TEMP_OBJECT_STORAGE_SCHEMA KM option to designate temporary storage location.
This LKM has to be used in combination with Oracle or generic SQL IKM.
Specify the name of logical schema defining the location the temporary file will be stored in Object Storage staging area. This must be a Object Storage technology logical schema.
Set this property to True if you want to compress source data before loading into Object Storage. Additional options COMPRESSION_TYPE and KEEP_SOURCE_FILES define compression preferences.
Select the type of compression you want to apply on source data before loadining into Object Storage.
Keep original source files after compression(True/False)
Set to True (default) if you want to compress files and keep originals. Note that gzip supports keep option starting from version 1.6.
